1
00:01:42,940 --> 00:01:45,860
Run for Young

2
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:14,940
You want some?

3
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:17,780
No no, I'm fine, thanks.

4
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:21,900
When was the first time you shaved?

5
00:02:22,980 --> 00:02:24,020
Last...last year.

6
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:25,460
Who taught you?

7
00:02:25,740 --> 00:02:27,060
Doggo's old man.

8
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:28,580
You three,

9
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:30,220
rub this soap water

10
00:02:31,220 --> 00:02:31,840
on your face.

11
00:02:35,420 --> 00:02:36,220
More!

12
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:37,300
Alright.

13
00:02:41,580 --> 00:02:42,660
Next,

14
00:02:42,660 --> 00:02:44,820
pick up the shaver I gave you.

15
00:02:51,020 --> 00:02:51,620
Shave!

16
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:55,580
Go ahead!

17
00:02:55,940 --> 00:02:57,100
What're you afraid of?

18
00:03:07,140 --> 00:03:08,780
You finally learned how to shave!

19
00:03:09,940 --> 00:03:10,600
Jiao!

20
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:11,860
Do you want a shave too?

21
00:03:11,940 --> 00:03:13,500
Com'on!

22
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:15,100
No no no.

23
00:03:15,460 --> 00:03:16,980
Not for me, not for me.

24
00:03:16,980 --> 00:03:18,780
No no no no no.

25
00:03:18,980 --> 00:03:20,100
What the heck are you doing, shaving a girl?

26
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,180
Shave me if you want!

27
00:03:21,220 --> 00:03:22,100
Yeah, go ahead and shave him.

28
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:22,740
C'mon!

29
00:03:23,060 --> 00:03:23,660
Here we go!

30
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:24,420
Come!

31
00:03:26,180 --> 00:03:27,460
My beard's longer than yours!

32
00:03:29,660 --> 00:03:30,820
You should come to me to learn shaving!

33
00:03:32,060 --> 00:03:33,580
Yeah, you need a shaving.

34
00:03:34,460 --> 00:03:35,660
You can pull it out just like this.

35
00:03:41,260 --> 00:03:46,260
Episode 9 Everyone Needs to Prepare Their Funniest Joke

36
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:48,940
How does it feel to suddenly have your old man around?

37
00:03:50,060 --> 00:03:50,900
Tell the truth!

38
00:03:51,060 --> 00:03:51,740
Yeah, tell the truth!

39
00:03:52,620 --> 00:03:53,780
It feels very strange.

40
00:03:54,180 --> 00:03:55,260
Very unfamiliar,

41
00:03:55,580 --> 00:03:56,860
even though I know he's my old man.

42
00:03:57,980 --> 00:03:59,020
What's strange about that?

43
00:03:59,940 --> 00:04:00,540
Well,

44
00:04:00,780 --> 00:04:02,340
I know he's my dad and I should be closer to him,

45
00:04:03,260 --> 00:04:04,420
but I just can't do it.

46
00:04:04,460 --> 00:04:05,460
Take your time.

47
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:06,780
You've only just got a dad.

48
00:04:07,220 --> 00:04:08,220
The start is always the most difficult.

49
00:04:10,260 --> 00:04:12,220
But why did your old man disappear for so long?

50
00:04:12,540 --> 00:04:13,900
Mom said he got lost.

51
00:04:14,260 --> 00:04:15,420
Lost for what?

52
00:04:15,420 --> 00:04:16,220
He's a grown-up man.

53
00:04:17,220 --> 00:04:19,540
Maybe it's just the world outside is very attractive.

54
00:04:19,540 --> 00:04:21,020
Why did he come back then?

55
00:04:21,340 --> 00:04:21,940
Well, you see,

56
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:23,620
the world outside can also be very frustrating.

57
00:04:24,060 --> 00:04:24,940
What do you mean?

58
00:04:25,260 --> 00:04:25,940
Never mind, you won't understand.

59
00:04:29,660 --> 00:04:30,660
I'm so jealous of you.

60
00:04:31,019 --> 00:04:31,740
Why's that?

61
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:33,660
Your all have your parents around.

62
00:04:33,860 --> 00:04:35,220
Well, your parents are around too.

63
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:36,700
They just don't live together.

64
00:04:37,460 --> 00:04:39,260
Besides, you have us with you!

65
00:04:39,460 --> 00:04:40,260
Yeah, you're right!

66
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:41,380
You're right!

67
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:42,300
Let's go!

68
00:04:45,980 --> 00:04:46,700
Ouch!

69
00:04:48,180 --> 00:04:50,220
Enough, enough!

70
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:52,500
That hurt!

71
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:53,220
Oh so you know it hurts now?

72
00:04:53,580 --> 00:04:54,180
Of course I do!

73
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:55,260
You!

74
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:00,340
Chen Yuanyuan!

75
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:04,220
What is it?

76
00:05:04,780 --> 00:05:06,380
It's the last term. Study hard!

77
00:05:06,980 --> 00:05:07,980
The same to you!

78
00:05:08,060 --> 00:05:09,780
Stop scheming for Ding Rongliang.

79
00:05:10,020 --> 00:05:10,860
Why?

80
00:05:10,860 --> 00:05:11,820
He's my pal,

81
00:05:11,820 --> 00:05:12,860
of course I need to help him.

82
00:05:16,940 --> 00:05:18,140
Why are you pissing her off?

83
00:05:18,980 --> 00:05:20,220
You don't understand.

84
00:05:20,460 --> 00:05:22,260
If you can't make her eyes red when you meet again,

85
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:23,820
at least you have to make her cheeks red.

86
00:05:24,980 --> 00:05:25,820
Really?

87
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:27,180
Of course!

88
00:05:27,420 --> 00:05:28,100
Look at her.

89
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:29,940
So pissed her cheeks are red like an apple.

90
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:34,460
Well, what's the point of that?

91
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:35,700
My Teaty,

92
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:38,340
since when did you start pondering the meaning of things?

93
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:40,540
I!

94
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:44,260
Teaty!

95
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:54,580
They're together now?

96
00:05:55,460 --> 00:05:56,780
That's right, we're together now!

97
00:05:58,460 --> 00:05:59,260
I remember last term,

98
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:00,780
when you and Anran walked up like this

99
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:01,740
we were staring at the two of you

100
00:06:01,740 --> 00:06:02,660
like they did to us just then.

101
00:06:03,460 --> 00:06:04,140
What were you staring at about us?

102
00:06:05,180 --> 00:06:07,180
Well, it's just you two looked very Romeo and Juliet.

103
00:06:08,980 --> 00:06:10,660
The two of us look very Romeo and Juliet too!

104
00:06:13,660 --> 00:06:16,220
Aw, I didn't mean it that way.

105
00:06:16,220 --> 00:06:17,980
You're so outspoken.

106
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:21,340
It's not good.

107
00:06:21,340 --> 00:06:22,540
Hurry up, you two brothers!

108
00:06:24,140 --> 00:06:25,260
I'm sorry, Jiao.

109
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:26,940
Two brothers. What?

110
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:28,820
Stop there!

111
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:30,780
Doggo!

112
00:06:32,220 --> 00:06:33,220
I bought this for you.

113
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:34,460
Thank you.

114
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:36,620
DOGGO IS AN A-HOLE

115
00:06:37,940 --> 00:06:38,780
Again!

116
00:06:38,980 --> 00:06:40,020
Happy new school term.

117
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:41,820
Happy new school term!

118
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:43,940
By the way, you've got any plan for the new term?

119
00:06:44,340 --> 00:06:45,780
What plans can I have?

120
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:47,020
Just preparing to go abroad.

121
00:06:51,260 --> 00:06:52,020
So you've decided?

122
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:53,380
Yep.

123
00:06:53,940 --> 00:06:54,860
But I'll make sure to help you

124
00:06:54,860 --> 00:06:56,500
with revision before I leave.

125
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:58,100
Besides, running marathon will earn you bonus points.

126
00:06:58,260 --> 00:06:59,620
You will surely have a college to go.

127
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:00,540
Me?

128
00:07:00,740 --> 00:07:01,700
Going to college?

129
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:03,500
I'm being serious!

130
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:04,500
You should take it seriously too.

131
00:07:07,420 --> 00:07:09,140
Well... I... I'll... I'll try my best...

132
00:07:09,580 --> 00:07:11,660
Don't just say it to brush me off!

133
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:18,380
Oh,

134
00:07:18,660 --> 00:07:19,580
since we are deskmates

135
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:20,780
and you gave me a gift,

136
00:07:20,780 --> 00:07:21,980
should I give you something in return?

137
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:22,860
No need for that.

138
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:23,940
If you study hard

139
00:07:24,140 --> 00:07:25,300
and don't waste my efforts in one-on-one tutoring for you

140
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:26,540
that's the best present I'll get.

141
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:28,540
Besides,

142
00:07:28,540 --> 00:07:30,180
I don't like pork liver that much.

143
00:07:33,540 --> 00:07:34,500
New term,

144
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:35,980
new start.

145
00:07:36,660 --> 00:07:39,500
Our team needs to have a new goal.

146
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:41,260
Coach, what new goal?

147
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:43,420
The bonus points for College Entrance Exam, obviously!

148
00:07:43,780 --> 00:07:45,020
Your intention's not pure at all!

149
00:07:45,020 --> 00:07:46,860
Exactly! We only care about sportsmanship.

150
00:07:48,820 --> 00:07:49,940
That's enough.

151
00:07:50,820 --> 00:07:52,820
You two are the slowest of the team.

152
00:07:53,180 --> 00:07:53,780
That's right.

153
00:07:54,460 --> 00:07:56,060
You can't even be sure you'd finish the race,

154
00:07:56,060 --> 00:07:57,100
let alone sportsmanship.

155
00:07:58,820 --> 00:07:59,900
There's a race in May,

156
00:08:00,820 --> 00:08:02,060
you all know that?

157
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:03,060
Yes.

158
00:08:03,060 --> 00:08:04,140
The rule of the race is this.

159
00:08:04,420 --> 00:08:05,140
Listen carefully.

160
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:08,180
You have to start at the starting point.

161
00:08:08,740 --> 00:08:11,060
The sum of the time

162
00:08:11,060 --> 00:08:12,060
of each member

163
00:08:12,060 --> 00:08:13,620
is the final result of your team.

164
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:15,060
Understood?

165
00:08:15,060 --> 00:08:15,900
Yes, sir.

166
00:08:16,820 --> 00:08:17,780
Understood?

167
00:08:17,780 --> 00:08:18,700
Yes, sir!

168
00:09:27,420 --> 00:09:28,100
What's the matter with you?

169
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:29,580
Nothing.

170
00:09:30,220 --> 00:09:31,340
I just want to

171
00:09:31,340 --> 00:09:32,060
sit here by myself a little longer.

172
00:09:32,700 --> 00:09:34,260
Is it because of your old man?

173
00:09:37,540 --> 00:09:39,300
You really don't like him, do you?

174
00:09:39,940 --> 00:09:40,700
It's not like that.

175
00:09:41,020 --> 00:09:41,860
It's just that...

176
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:43,580
My old man's a stranger to me, and it's kinda awkward.

177
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:45,020
It's not that I don't like him.

178
00:09:45,460 --> 00:09:46,900
What's so awkward about being around your own dad?

179
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:48,260
You think everyone

180
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:49,740
gets along with their dad so well like you do?

181
00:09:50,620 --> 00:09:51,620
Do I get along with my old man so well?

182
00:09:52,420 --> 00:09:53,380
Don't you?

183
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:56,020
You really don't appreciate what you have.

184
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:02,340
Anran.

185
00:10:04,940 --> 00:10:05,620
C'mon!

186
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:07,580
Anran!

187
00:10:08,420 --> 00:10:10,420
Doggo wants to walk you home. Is that ok?

188
00:10:12,220 --> 00:10:12,980
Ok.

189
00:10:22,820 --> 00:10:24,340
What's this for?

190
00:10:24,340 --> 00:10:25,020
For listening to music.

191
00:10:25,020 --> 00:10:25,980
Mp3.

192
00:10:26,260 --> 00:10:27,220
Where do you put the cassette then?

193
00:10:27,380 --> 00:10:28,460
It doesn't need cassettes.

194
00:10:28,780 --> 00:10:29,780
Where do you store the songs then?

195
00:10:29,940 --> 00:10:31,660
You just download them from the computer.

196
00:10:33,020 --> 00:10:34,380
Well, it's 2005 already.

197
00:10:34,380 --> 00:10:35,380
Things are surely different now.

198
00:10:35,740 --> 00:10:36,460
Yeah.

199
00:10:36,460 --> 00:10:37,700
Technology's big these days.

200
00:10:45,340 --> 00:10:46,420
I know this song!

201
00:10:46,620 --> 00:10:47,540
Which song?

202
00:10:49,620 --> 00:10:50,420
I'll sing it out for you.

203
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:40,780
You should sign up, Jiao Jiao

204
00:11:41,340 --> 00:11:42,420
What are you talking about?

205
00:11:42,700 --> 00:11:44,460
You want to become a Super Girl, don't you?

206
00:11:44,660 --> 00:11:45,340
Go for it.

207
00:11:45,620 --> 00:11:47,460
Who said I wanted to become a Super Girl?

208
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:53,260
I only want to become a normal girl.

209
00:11:53,260 --> 00:11:53,860
What's wrong with a normal girl

210
00:11:53,860 --> 00:11:55,500
signing up for the Super Girl audition?

211
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:56,580
A lot wrong!

212
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:57,400
I don't get it.

213
00:11:57,700 --> 00:11:59,020
A normal person's afraid of many things.

214
00:11:59,380 --> 00:12:00,820
A normal person is afraid of being in front of people.

215
00:12:01,060 --> 00:12:02,940
A normal person has to lead a normal life.

216
00:12:03,420 --> 00:12:04,140
Who said a normal person

217
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:05,780
can't do what they want?

218
00:12:10,740 --> 00:12:11,980
You're so weird.

219
00:12:11,980 --> 00:12:12,820
Why don't you go yourself?

220
00:12:13,420 --> 00:12:14,420
I don't want to sign up.

221
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:54,260
Doggo went home with Anran.

222
00:12:55,260 --> 00:12:56,860
Hercules Jiao went home with Ma Tian.

223
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,200
Well, at least,

224
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:01,820
I still have you to walk home with me.

225
00:13:02,660 --> 00:13:03,260
Hold on a sec...

226
00:13:04,340 --> 00:13:04,940
What is it?

227
00:13:04,980 --> 00:13:05,820
Go home yourself!

228
00:13:06,980 --> 00:13:08,260
Hey, How could you do that?

229
00:13:20,980 --> 00:13:21,620
Hey, what a surprise!

230
00:13:23,780 --> 00:13:24,420
Long time no see.

231
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:28,020
How have you been

232
00:13:28,380 --> 00:13:29,260
since we last met?

233
00:13:29,260 --> 00:13:30,140
Yeah, I'm fine.

234
00:13:30,140 --> 00:13:30,980
Old man, you know,

235
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:31,900
so weak.

236
00:13:34,180 --> 00:13:34,820
I mean...

237
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:35,500
the fist.

238
00:13:36,340 --> 00:13:37,140
Good you weren't hurt.

239
00:13:37,580 --> 00:13:38,740
We don't run into each other everyday,

240
00:13:39,020 --> 00:13:39,860
and the weather's so good today.

241
00:13:40,340 --> 00:13:41,460
Can I buy you something to eat?

242
00:13:42,740 --> 00:13:43,660
I'm fine.

243
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:44,900
I'm waiting for someone.

244
00:13:45,380 --> 00:13:46,020
Who?

245
00:13:47,580 --> 00:13:48,420
The same guy?

246
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:54,660
Where does he normally take you for dinner?

247
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:57,700
Those new rich are never very creative anyway.

248
00:13:58,740 --> 00:14:00,260
He's so fricking old.

249
00:14:00,260 --> 00:14:01,380
Why are you doing this?

250
00:14:01,380 --> 00:14:02,020
Right?

251
00:14:02,340 --> 00:14:03,500
Why can't you be like me,

252
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:04,380
put your efforts into studying,

253
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:05,980
go to college

254
00:14:05,980 --> 00:14:07,300
and then find a proper job?

255
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:10,300
Why can't you just go home and do your homework?

256
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:11,700
I finished my homework long ago!

257
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:13,900
Don't be with him anymore.

258
00:14:14,060 --> 00:14:15,380
I don't think he can make you happy.

259
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:17,420
He doesn't look like someone cultured and educated.

260
00:14:23,180 --> 00:14:24,580
"Cultured and educated", ugh, coming from you?

261
00:14:25,060 --> 00:14:26,620
"Find a proper job"?

262
00:14:29,780 --> 00:14:30,900
Who do you think you are

263
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:32,260
to give me a lesson?

264
00:14:32,760 --> 00:14:33,360
I'll teach you some...

265
00:14:37,860 --> 00:14:39,860
What are you, a future student of Tsinghua uni

266
00:14:39,860 --> 00:14:40,820
or Peking uni?

267
00:14:47,060 --> 00:14:47,740
Hey!

268
00:14:49,140 --> 00:14:50,900
If I get into Tsinghua or Peking,

269
00:14:51,060 --> 00:14:52,740
will you have another look at me?

270
00:15:02,340 --> 00:15:03,220
Don't worry,

271
00:15:03,220 --> 00:15:04,700
your dad will be well very soon.

272
00:15:06,420 --> 00:15:07,340
It feels

273
00:15:07,820 --> 00:15:08,860
a bit strange to me.

274
00:15:09,020 --> 00:15:09,820
What's strange?

275
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:11,500
When you were little,

276
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:13,420
I used to push you around like this

277
00:15:13,740 --> 00:15:15,100
and let you play in the stroller.

278
00:15:16,340 --> 00:15:17,060
Yeah, I remember.

279
00:15:17,340 --> 00:15:18,100
It was something like

280
00:15:19,260 --> 00:15:19,880
this.

281
00:15:20,620 --> 00:15:21,260
Like this.

282
00:15:28,540 --> 00:15:29,540
Do you think

283
00:15:30,060 --> 00:15:30,980
every person

284
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:32,340
has a different side?

285
00:15:33,860 --> 00:15:35,660
You'll know the person, the face, but not the heart.

286
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:38,420
That's not what I mean.

287
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:39,580
It's the same.

288
00:15:43,580 --> 00:15:44,260
Careful.

289
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:47,760
Ehh,

290
00:15:48,420 --> 00:15:49,100
Shenxi.

291
00:15:51,260 --> 00:15:52,100
I saw that

292
00:15:52,460 --> 00:15:53,860
you were shaving with scissors.

293
00:15:55,420 --> 00:15:56,300
It's not

294
00:15:57,020 --> 00:15:57,740
very convenient.

295
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,460
So I bought

296
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:02,260
this

297
00:16:02,620 --> 00:16:03,420
electric shaver for you.

298
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:06,300
You even wrapped it.

299
00:16:07,660 --> 00:16:08,660
It's my first present to you.

300
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:10,380
I wanted it to be like the real thing.

301
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:11,740
I see.

302
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:13,380
Thank you.

303
00:16:14,380 --> 00:16:15,000
You're welcome.

304
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:17,860
Careful.

305
00:16:17,860 --> 00:16:19,900
Can you two help me bring over the dishes?

306
00:16:21,820 --> 00:16:22,440
Sure.

307
00:16:22,740 --> 00:16:24,540
One person is enough.

308
00:16:24,660 --> 00:16:25,340
- I'll go. - I'll go.

309
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:29,060
- You go then. - You go then.

310
00:16:30,060 --> 00:16:31,020
I'll go!

311
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:32,340
My god.

312
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:35,340
Sit then.

313
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:36,340
Yeah, have a seat.

314
00:16:38,180 --> 00:16:39,580
Look how capable your mom is.

315
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,100
Careful.

316
00:16:43,580 --> 00:16:45,460
If you two keep being this polite

317
00:16:45,820 --> 00:16:46,860
the food is getting cold.

318
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:49,260
Let's start then.

319
00:16:53,220 --> 00:16:54,180
Oh, by the way,

320
00:16:54,420 --> 00:16:55,700
the boy that walked you home,

321
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:57,020
is he the one that came to our house

322
00:16:57,020 --> 00:16:58,340
at your birthday party?

323
00:16:58,860 --> 00:16:59,860
You saw us?

324
00:16:59,860 --> 00:17:00,900
Of course.

325
00:17:00,900 --> 00:17:02,860
Can't quite ignore that kind of singing.

326
00:17:05,340 --> 00:17:06,180
I just want to ask you

327
00:17:06,940 --> 00:17:08,140
if he's not mad at me.

328
00:17:08,780 --> 00:17:09,780
Why would he be mad?

329
00:17:10,980 --> 00:17:12,740
Do you remember that at your birthday party

330
00:17:13,020 --> 00:17:14,980
daddy had a little too much to drink

331
00:17:15,179 --> 00:17:16,139
and said a little too much as well.

332
00:17:16,460 --> 00:17:17,580
Pretty annoying, right?

333
00:17:18,300 --> 00:17:20,100
Don't worry, dad, he's really nice.

334
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:21,300
He won't be petty over these things.

335
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:23,460
He may look like a careless one,

336
00:17:23,460 --> 00:17:25,139
but he's actually very caring

337
00:17:25,139 --> 00:17:26,940
and he puts others before himself.

338
00:17:26,940 --> 00:17:28,060
He's not

339
00:17:28,060 --> 00:17:28,940
what he appears to be.

340
00:17:29,179 --> 00:17:30,460
- People just... - Oh, you'll need

341
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:33,260
to prepare the materials for studying abroad.

342
00:17:33,659 --> 00:17:34,659
Don't worry.

343
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:36,740
I'm preparing everything carefully.

344
00:17:36,980 --> 00:17:38,300
Besides, him and I

345
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:40,180
are just classmate plus deskmate, nothing special.

346
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:42,740
We are the "one-on-one" study match, so we help each other.

347
00:17:43,180 --> 00:17:44,020
We were from the...

348
00:17:44,020 --> 00:17:45,580
The "one-on-one" study match.

349
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:46,620
I see.

350
00:17:46,940 --> 00:17:47,540
That's good.

351
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:49,940
I think this boy...

352
00:17:51,660 --> 00:17:52,820
How can I put it...

353
00:18:00,420 --> 00:18:01,380
Has a good voice.

354
00:18:08,580 --> 00:18:09,660
Such a pretty pair of shoes!

355
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:19,180
What's so good in the magazine?

356
00:18:24,980 --> 00:18:26,380
It's 2005 already.

357
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:28,460
And?

358
00:18:29,340 --> 00:18:30,220
Technology's big these days.

359
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:32,940
What the heck does that have to do with me?

360
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:34,980
I'm a pork butcher.

361
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:36,580
All I need is a butcher knife.

362
00:18:37,220 --> 00:18:38,420
Is technology gonna be so big

363
00:18:38,420 --> 00:18:39,340
that they're gonna invent

364
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:41,180
electric butcher knives?

365
00:18:42,940 --> 00:18:44,380
My classmates use that little box

366
00:18:44,380 --> 00:18:44,980
to listen to music

367
00:18:45,260 --> 00:18:46,340
and they have high-tech smart phones.

368
00:18:46,740 --> 00:18:48,100
I don't even have a PHS.

369
00:18:49,580 --> 00:18:51,340
Well, but you're already so smart.

370
00:18:52,460 --> 00:18:54,020
So clever and good at study.

371
00:18:54,020 --> 00:18:55,060
You have good grades too.

372
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:57,260
You don't need a PHS at all.

373
00:18:58,100 --> 00:18:58,860
Stingy.

374
00:18:59,260 --> 00:19:01,300
God knows how you managed to win over Aunty Zhang.

375
00:19:02,820 --> 00:19:04,900
I send her meat for years on end.

376
00:19:05,180 --> 00:19:06,500
Human heart is flesh and meat as well, you see.

377
00:19:06,580 --> 00:19:08,100
Pork meat?

378
00:19:10,420 --> 00:19:11,040
By the way,

379
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:13,140
when is Aunty Zhang moving in with us?

380
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:18,580
We'll talk about that

381
00:19:19,220 --> 00:19:20,260
after you little brat goes to college.

382
00:19:23,180 --> 00:19:24,980
You think I'd have a college to go to?

383
00:19:31,980 --> 00:19:32,580
By...

384
00:19:32,580 --> 00:19:33,460
By the way.

385
00:19:35,580 --> 00:19:37,540
Kids of other houses are all pretty decent.

386
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:42,380
Would you sometimes be ashamed of me?

387
00:19:49,060 --> 00:19:50,940
Dads of other houses

388
00:19:50,940 --> 00:19:52,300
all dress up nice and fancy.

389
00:19:53,620 --> 00:19:55,300
I'm just a butcher.

390
00:19:57,860 --> 00:20:00,020
Would you sometimes

391
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:01,500
be ashamed of me then?

392
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:03,100
No.

393
00:20:11,540 --> 00:20:12,860
You remember when you were little

394
00:20:13,180 --> 00:20:14,580
I told you to

395
00:20:14,620 --> 00:20:16,140
never mention at school

396
00:20:16,220 --> 00:20:18,380
that I was a butcher at the market.

397
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:21,540
But then one afternoon,

398
00:20:21,980 --> 00:20:24,220
you brought over a whole bunch of classmates to my stall

399
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:26,820
and asked me to cut them each a little piece of pork

400
00:20:27,140 --> 00:20:27,760
as a gift.

401
00:20:28,900 --> 00:20:30,500
I wanted to show off, you know.

402
00:20:30,580 --> 00:20:31,700
I know.

403
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:33,500
From that time, I thought that

404
00:20:34,460 --> 00:20:35,780
you might not be the brightest,

405
00:20:36,220 --> 00:20:37,780
but I'm very happy to have you.

406
00:20:38,060 --> 00:20:38,700
Right?

407
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:41,980
Why are we bringing this up?

408
00:20:43,140 --> 00:20:44,060
I dunno.

409
00:21:06,340 --> 00:21:06,940
Li Anran.

410
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:08,800
Tu Jun.

411
00:21:09,580 --> 00:21:10,260
I want to go to college.

412
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:12,740
I support you.

413
00:21:13,020 --> 00:21:14,300
I want to be a uni student like you.

414
00:21:14,380 --> 00:21:15,780
Otherwise, I'll have to be a butcher.

415
00:21:16,580 --> 00:21:18,300
Where do you think the best universities in China are?

416
00:21:19,140 --> 00:21:20,580
Tsinghua uni and Peking uni, I think.

417
00:21:20,900 --> 00:21:21,940
But they have nothing to do with you, you know.

418
00:21:21,980 --> 00:21:22,600
I know.

419
00:21:23,380 --> 00:21:24,540
I'd be lucky if there's any college that wants me.

420
00:21:24,980 --> 00:21:25,700
That's true.

421
00:21:27,140 --> 00:21:28,820
Why don't you apply to Tsinghua and Peking?

422
00:21:28,820 --> 00:21:29,660
The UK is so far away.

423
00:21:30,340 --> 00:21:31,540
It's not like I'm not coming back.

424
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:32,580
I just wanted to go and see for myself.

425
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:33,940
In four years?

426
00:21:35,140 --> 00:21:36,660
If I go for a Master's Degree or PhD

427
00:21:36,660 --> 00:21:37,700
it'll be longer.

428
00:21:39,180 --> 00:21:39,800
Hong much longer?

429
00:21:41,220 --> 00:21:41,900
Many years.

430
00:21:48,420 --> 00:21:49,820
Wouldn't you miss home?

431
00:21:50,460 --> 00:21:51,180
Think about it.

432
00:21:51,820 --> 00:21:52,820
You have your parents,

433
00:21:52,940 --> 00:21:53,620
family,

434
00:21:53,940 --> 00:21:54,560
friends.

435
00:21:55,020 --> 00:21:55,900
and deskmate, of course.

436
00:21:56,420 --> 00:21:57,180
Think about it.

437
00:21:57,380 --> 00:21:58,300
If you went abroad,

438
00:21:58,340 --> 00:21:59,140
what are they gonna do?

439
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:00,100
Right?

440
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:01,100
So...

441
00:22:01,100 --> 00:22:02,220
I will miss home.

442
00:22:05,580 --> 00:22:07,060
So you have to think it through carefully!

443
00:22:07,980 --> 00:22:09,500
Worry about yourself first!

444
00:22:09,500 --> 00:22:10,700
You want to become a college student, don't you?

445
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:12,060
I wouldn't want to see that when I become one,

446
00:22:12,060 --> 00:22:13,300
you're still selling pork.

447
00:22:18,060 --> 00:22:18,940
Tu Jun, stand up!

448
00:22:20,180 --> 00:22:21,260
- Study, - assiduously!

449
00:22:21,260 --> 00:22:22,340
- Rise up upon, - the roar of the rooster!

450
00:22:22,340 --> 00:22:23,300
- Heaven rewards, - the diligent ones!

451
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:24,440
- Sit down! - Yes.

452
00:22:26,580 --> 00:22:27,460
What is it, Jiao?

453
00:22:29,300 --> 00:22:31,180
You have to study hard if you want to go to uni

454
00:22:31,460 --> 00:22:32,660
and cut the chitchat.

455
00:22:32,940 --> 00:22:34,340
You won't get into uni with talking.

456
00:22:35,780 --> 00:22:36,580
Thank you, Jiao!

457
00:23:02,780 --> 00:23:03,420
He said

458
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:05,580
the answer to this question is this.

459
00:23:12,940 --> 00:23:15,100
RISE UP UPON THE ROAR OF THE COCK

460
00:23:16,100 --> 00:23:17,340
STUDY ASSIDUOUSLY

461
00:23:32,820 --> 00:23:34,420
I heard there'd be bonus points
to the College Entrance Exam if we won.

462
00:23:34,420 --> 00:23:35,180
Is that real?

463
00:23:35,860 --> 00:23:36,660
My bro,

464
00:23:37,020 --> 00:23:38,060
if we had those few extra points,

465
00:23:38,060 --> 00:23:39,780
that'd be a pleasant add-on for me,

466
00:23:40,020 --> 00:23:41,620
but wouldn't do much in your case.

467
00:23:41,620 --> 00:23:42,300
What do you mean?

468
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:43,380
He means

469
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:44,500
a few extra points wouldn't do nothing for you,

470
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:45,700
since your grades are so bad.

471
00:23:46,260 --> 00:23:47,620
It's better than nothing!

472
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:49,740
So you care about bonus points now?

473
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:50,940
That's right.

474
00:23:50,940 --> 00:23:52,060
I'm going to college!

475
00:23:53,780 --> 00:23:54,660
What're you laughing at!

476
00:23:55,380 --> 00:23:56,140
Maybe you won't even be able to

477
00:23:56,140 --> 00:23:57,180
take the College Entrance Examination!

478
00:24:13,540 --> 00:24:14,180
You little brat, I'm

479
00:24:15,260 --> 00:24:17,140
going to Bishan to get some pork.

480
00:24:17,660 --> 00:24:18,580
Won't be back till late.

481
00:24:19,220 --> 00:24:20,500
Why all the way to Bishan?

482
00:24:20,740 --> 00:24:22,020
It's cheap there!

483
00:24:23,060 --> 00:24:24,140
Don't be sniveling for

484
00:24:24,260 --> 00:24:25,020
being left alone in the house.

485
00:24:26,340 --> 00:24:27,780
I'd love to be left alone in the house!

486
00:24:31,540 --> 00:24:33,060
I bought you a new pair of shoes.

487
00:24:33,340 --> 00:24:34,220
They're on the shelf.

488
00:24:35,060 --> 00:24:35,820
I've told you many times!

489
00:24:35,820 --> 00:24:37,340
Better if you give me the money and let me do the shopping.

490
00:24:37,340 --> 00:24:38,940
The shoes you buy aren't good-looking at all.

491
00:24:38,940 --> 00:24:39,860
I never like them.

492
00:24:40,340 --> 00:24:42,180
How do you know you won't like them without trying?

493
00:24:42,660 --> 00:24:43,620
It's not the first time!

494
00:24:43,620 --> 00:24:44,300
I don't even need to try anymore.

495
00:24:44,740 --> 00:24:45,740
Whatever, it's up to you.

496
00:24:46,340 --> 00:24:47,540
I'm only buying these for you

497
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:48,980
because you do marathon.

498
00:24:49,820 --> 00:24:50,500
I'm telling you,

499
00:24:50,980 --> 00:24:52,100
I can run just as fast

500
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:53,180
on these.

501
00:24:54,100 --> 00:24:54,700
Boasting!

502
00:24:55,260 --> 00:24:56,820
Boasting doesn't cost money, after all.

503
00:24:56,820 --> 00:24:57,480
Keep it on.

504
00:24:57,620 --> 00:24:58,540
I'm not boasting!

505
00:24:58,660 --> 00:25:00,780
We're sure to win this race.

506
00:25:01,980 --> 00:25:03,020
Really?

507
00:25:03,180 --> 00:25:04,060
For sure!

508
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:05,340
Then,

509
00:25:05,540 --> 00:25:06,700
I can hang the award certificate

510
00:25:07,140 --> 00:25:08,780
on the wall

511
00:25:09,100 --> 00:25:12,140
like other parents?

512
00:25:15,700 --> 00:25:16,320
That's right!

513
00:25:16,920 --> 00:25:17,520
I don't believe it.

514
00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:18,700
See ya later.

515
00:25:20,300 --> 00:25:20,900
Butcher!

516
00:25:22,660 --> 00:25:23,260
What now?

517
00:25:24,100 --> 00:25:25,220
We're taking the College Entrance Examination soon.

518
00:25:25,540 --> 00:25:26,140
What do you reckon I should study?

519
00:25:26,820 --> 00:25:29,220
What kind of college'd admit you?

520
00:25:29,860 --> 00:25:30,660
Go kill pigs, I'd say.

521
00:25:57,540 --> 00:25:58,780
My boy, I'm telling you,

522
00:25:59,780 --> 00:26:01,340
you're so inconsistent.

523
00:26:01,580 --> 00:26:02,860
No determination whatsoever.

524
00:26:03,340 --> 00:26:04,100
Why's that?

525
00:26:04,420 --> 00:26:05,100
Why's what?

526
00:26:05,540 --> 00:26:06,500
You told me yourself

527
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:08,700
that you wanted to keep your beard like the movie stars

528
00:26:08,780 --> 00:26:09,380
and now you're shaving already.

529
00:26:09,980 --> 00:26:11,660
You can't hold on to it for more than a few days.

530
00:26:11,940 --> 00:26:12,780
That's not it!

531
00:26:14,540 --> 00:26:16,300
Dad gave me this electric shaver.

532
00:26:17,300 --> 00:26:18,900
It's my first time using a gift from my dad.

533
00:26:19,820 --> 00:26:20,440
That's right.

534
00:26:21,020 --> 00:26:23,180
It's a present to our son.

535
00:26:26,020 --> 00:26:27,260
It's so touching.

536
00:26:30,060 --> 00:26:32,220
I'm so unaccustomed to you

537
00:26:32,220 --> 00:26:33,220
calling each other

538
00:26:33,220 --> 00:26:35,060
dad and son.

539
00:26:38,340 --> 00:26:38,960
Dad?

540
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:42,100
Here, have one.

541
00:26:42,420 --> 00:26:43,020
It's very sweet.

542
00:26:50,700 --> 00:26:51,940
Butcher left at noon

543
00:26:51,940 --> 00:26:53,380
and is still not back.

544
00:26:54,300 --> 00:26:55,100
It's the weekend.

545
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:56,660
Maybe it's the traffic.

546
00:26:58,100 --> 00:26:58,700
Your accent

547
00:26:58,700 --> 00:27:00,540
is more and more far off.

548
00:27:00,780 --> 00:27:02,580
I feel like I'm assimilated by you.

549
00:27:02,980 --> 00:27:04,260
What's wrong with my accent?

550
00:27:04,780 --> 00:27:05,780
When I was about six or seven,

551
00:27:05,780 --> 00:27:06,860
my old man brought me over

552
00:27:07,220 --> 00:27:08,620
and people were laughing at my accent.

553
00:27:09,060 --> 00:27:09,980
But my old man said

554
00:27:10,380 --> 00:27:11,820
my accent was the best of the best.

555
00:27:12,860 --> 00:27:13,780
He didn't mind at all.

556
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:16,220
My old man's pretty good to me.

557
00:27:17,820 --> 00:27:19,100
My old man's good to me too!

558
00:27:19,420 --> 00:27:20,020
Ohh,

559
00:27:20,340 --> 00:27:21,540
he bought me an electric shaver

560
00:27:21,540 --> 00:27:22,900
the other day.

561
00:27:24,940 --> 00:27:26,700
My old man's good to me too!

562
00:27:30,260 --> 00:27:31,380
In unspeakable ways!

563
00:27:37,380 --> 00:27:38,660
What're you looking at me for?

564
00:27:39,660 --> 00:27:40,780
My old man the butcher,

565
00:27:40,780 --> 00:27:41,860
you know how he's like.

566
00:27:42,260 --> 00:27:43,260
Scolds me every day,

567
00:27:43,780 --> 00:27:45,260
firing mouth guns and all that.

568
00:27:46,060 --> 00:27:47,180
Very stingy as well.

569
00:27:47,780 --> 00:27:49,620
Never buys me anything I want.

570
00:27:50,300 --> 00:27:51,540
Your old man is indeed a bit scary.

571
00:27:52,300 --> 00:27:52,980
That's true.

572
00:27:53,540 --> 00:27:54,460
Tall and bulky.

573
00:27:55,500 --> 00:27:56,860
Surely looks like a gangster to me.

574
00:27:58,340 --> 00:27:58,940
But!

575
00:28:03,340 --> 00:28:04,060
But...

576
00:28:06,100 --> 00:28:07,380
I think butcher's getting old.

577
00:28:09,780 --> 00:28:11,100
He ain't as scary as he used to be.

578
00:28:20,880 --> 00:28:21,500
Look!

579
00:28:22,360 --> 00:28:23,000
What?

580
00:28:23,540 --> 00:28:24,660
You remember when we were little

581
00:28:25,020 --> 00:28:26,860
we'd be jumping under the tree in turn

582
00:28:27,300 --> 00:28:29,140
to see who could reach the leaves.

583
00:28:48,540 --> 00:28:50,020
None of us could reach it back then.

584
00:28:51,900 --> 00:28:52,580
But now,

585
00:28:53,020 --> 00:28:54,020
easy peasy.

586
00:28:54,020 --> 00:28:54,660
That's right!

587
00:28:54,740 --> 00:28:55,500
Easy peasy!

588
00:28:57,300 --> 00:28:58,140
Silly.

589
00:28:58,140 --> 00:28:59,180
You silly!

590
00:29:01,300 --> 00:29:02,460
Don't you feel like we're grown-up all of a sudden?

591
00:29:04,020 --> 00:29:04,620
Yeah.

592
00:29:05,660 --> 00:29:07,780
So our moms and dads are getting old.

593
00:29:13,700 --> 00:29:15,260
I need to get into a college, don't I?

594
00:29:15,580 --> 00:29:17,460
Butcher said if I got into college

595
00:29:17,620 --> 00:29:19,460
he could live with Aunty Zhang then.

596
00:29:21,100 --> 00:29:22,020
Hurry up then!

597
00:29:22,340 --> 00:29:24,180
Maybe you'll have a little brother or sister soon.

598
00:29:24,660 --> 00:29:26,060
A second child?

599
00:29:26,340 --> 00:29:27,260
Maybe the birth-control policy

600
00:29:27,620 --> 00:29:28,620
will loosen up some day.

601
00:29:28,620 --> 00:29:29,500
Loosen your butt!

602
00:29:34,620 --> 00:29:37,220
What kind of college do you reckon we'd go to?

603
00:29:37,300 --> 00:29:39,500
You, college? With an IQ like this?

604
00:29:39,940 --> 00:29:41,620
You two aren't much different, to be fair.

605
00:29:42,300 --> 00:29:43,740
Same to you!

606
00:29:50,660 --> 00:29:52,220
Still not back at this hour.

607
00:29:52,780 --> 00:29:54,220
I wonder where he's wandering about.

608
00:30:08,260 --> 00:30:09,580
And the rain's so heavy.

609
00:30:21,100 --> 00:30:22,340
This goddamn weather.

610
00:30:23,620 --> 00:30:24,820
Pouring rain

611
00:30:25,180 --> 00:30:26,140
just when you're in a hurry.

612
00:30:45,020 --> 00:30:46,300
It's this late now.

613
00:30:46,300 --> 00:30:48,100
Butcher must be hungry when he comes home.

614
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:05,340
Boss,

615
00:31:05,340 --> 00:31:06,700
two rice noodles to go please.

616
00:31:07,260 --> 00:31:07,900
Why are you out so far for food

617
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:10,100
in this weather?

618
00:31:10,100 --> 00:31:12,180
I'm buying them for my old man.

619
00:31:12,780 --> 00:31:14,140
I'll wrap up for today after serving you.

620
00:31:19,420 --> 00:31:20,620
Such heavy rain.

621
00:32:05,500 --> 00:32:06,140
Butcher!

622
00:32:07,100 --> 00:32:07,740
Butcher!

623
00:32:07,820 --> 00:32:09,020
Don't scare me, butcher!

624
00:32:11,860 --> 00:32:12,980
You alright, butcher?

625
00:32:13,180 --> 00:32:14,100
Don't scare me, butcher!

626
00:32:14,580 --> 00:32:15,180
Butcher!

627
00:32:21,660 --> 00:32:22,540
Butcher!

628
00:32:23,860 --> 00:32:25,700
Wake up butcher!

629
00:32:26,380 --> 00:32:27,620
Get up butcher!

630
00:32:28,060 --> 00:32:28,660
Butcher!

631
00:32:34,140 --> 00:32:34,780
Butcher!

632
00:32:35,340 --> 00:32:36,180
Butcher!

633
00:32:36,620 --> 00:32:38,700
Anyone?

634
00:32:39,420 --> 00:32:40,180
Someone!

635
00:32:40,180 --> 00:32:41,660
Call the ambulance for me!

636
00:32:41,660 --> 00:32:42,980
Please!

637
00:32:43,140 --> 00:32:46,180
Someone! Anyone hear me?

638
00:32:46,540 --> 00:32:47,740
Help!

639
00:32:47,980 --> 00:32:50,100
Help me call the ambulance!

640
00:32:50,100 --> 00:32:52,420
Someone help us please...

641
00:32:53,980 --> 00:32:55,260
Help!

642
00:32:55,980 --> 00:32:57,740
Hurry!

643
00:32:58,260 --> 00:32:59,300
Get up butcher!

644
00:32:59,300 --> 00:33:00,740
Let's go home!

645
00:33:16,380 --> 00:33:17,060
Let's go.

646
00:33:43,860 --> 00:33:44,500
I'm telling you, old man,

647
00:33:45,140 --> 00:33:46,380
I asked over and over again for a cell phone

648
00:33:46,380 --> 00:33:46,980
but you just won't buy it

649
00:33:46,980 --> 00:33:47,900
whatever I said.

650
00:33:47,900 --> 00:33:48,580
And look what you got us into now.

651
00:33:48,580 --> 00:33:49,700
Can't blame anyone else but us two.

652
00:33:51,500 --> 00:33:52,260
Oh by the way, dad,

653
00:33:53,460 --> 00:33:55,220
I bought rice noodles for us just then.

654
00:33:55,220 --> 00:33:56,260
But now after all this drama

655
00:33:56,260 --> 00:33:57,900
neither of us can have it.

656
00:33:59,500 --> 00:34:01,860
Say something, dad.

657
00:34:09,500 --> 00:34:10,100
Dad,

658
00:34:10,660 --> 00:34:11,260
I get it now.

659
00:34:11,380 --> 00:34:13,140
You just want to see me suffer carrying you!

660
00:34:13,620 --> 00:34:15,260
Alright, don't scare me now.

661
00:34:15,420 --> 00:34:16,820
Wake up now!

662
00:34:17,780 --> 00:34:18,660
Son...

663
00:34:19,660 --> 00:34:20,980
Why don't you call me little brat now?

664
00:34:21,980 --> 00:34:24,020
Is it spring now?

665
00:34:25,340 --> 00:34:26,739
Yes, yes it's spring.

666
00:34:28,340 --> 00:34:30,460
If I accidentally passed away...

667
00:34:31,699 --> 00:34:34,340
you can bury me in spring,

668
00:34:36,820 --> 00:34:38,020
and by autumn,

669
00:34:38,020 --> 00:34:40,500
you can harvest a lot of old men.

670
00:34:40,900 --> 00:34:42,860
What're you talking about, dad!

671
00:34:43,900 --> 00:34:45,020
Not funny?

672
00:34:46,739 --> 00:34:47,360
Funny.

673
00:34:48,020 --> 00:34:48,640
Funny.

674
00:34:49,940 --> 00:34:51,219
When I was a little school boy,

675
00:34:52,060 --> 00:34:53,259
our teacher

676
00:34:55,100 --> 00:34:58,219
taught us to

677
00:34:58,219 --> 00:34:59,340
prepare the funniest joke

678
00:35:01,020 --> 00:35:03,020
of our life.

679
00:35:04,660 --> 00:35:06,900
This way, when we bid farewell,

680
00:35:08,060 --> 00:35:09,500
we could see the smiley face

681
00:35:10,100 --> 00:35:12,180
of our most beloved one.

682
00:35:16,420 --> 00:35:17,420
It's only a shame that

683
00:35:21,260 --> 00:35:23,500
I didn't have much time to prepare.

684
00:35:24,980 --> 00:35:26,300
I hope you won't mind.

685
00:35:51,060 --> 00:35:51,720
Dad?

686
00:35:53,540 --> 00:35:54,660
Dad, don't scare me!

687
00:35:54,660 --> 00:35:56,380
Wake up, dad!

688
00:35:57,020 --> 00:35:58,620
I'll take you to the hospital right now.

689
00:35:58,820 --> 00:36:00,260
I'll listen to you from now on.

690
00:36:00,300 --> 00:36:01,180
I'll listen to you.

691
00:36:01,620 --> 00:36:03,500
I'll watch the stall with you.

692
00:36:03,780 --> 00:36:04,980
I'll help you at the stall everyday

693
00:36:04,980 --> 00:36:06,580
so you won't have it so hard on yourself.

694
00:36:06,580 --> 00:36:07,540
Please, please.

695
00:36:08,140 --> 00:36:09,060
Please wake up.

696
00:36:09,060 --> 00:36:11,420
Don't leave me alone.

697
00:36:12,660 --> 00:36:14,060
Dad, please...

698
00:36:15,100 --> 00:36:17,620
Please wake up...

699
00:37:05,100 --> 00:37:05,740
Where's Doggo?

700
00:37:06,740 --> 00:37:07,340
No idea.

701
00:37:07,700 --> 00:37:09,540
I knocked on his door this morning but nobody answered.

702
00:37:09,540 --> 00:37:10,580
I thought he came by himself first.

703
00:37:11,900 --> 00:37:13,700
It must be that his old man got home real late

704
00:37:13,700 --> 00:37:14,620
last night and woke him up,

705
00:37:14,620 --> 00:37:15,580
so he overslept.

706
00:37:16,420 --> 00:37:17,020
That must be it.

707
00:37:17,420 --> 00:37:19,820
How could he come here without waiting for us anyway?

708
00:37:20,180 --> 00:37:21,460
You fool, Teaty!

709
00:37:22,660 --> 00:37:23,780
You fool!

710
00:37:25,980 --> 00:37:26,600
The coach is here!

711
00:37:26,940 --> 00:37:27,600
The coach is here.

712
00:37:30,300 --> 00:37:31,660
The coach looks so serious today.

713
00:37:31,700 --> 00:37:32,780
He must be in a bad mood today.

714
00:37:33,340 --> 00:37:34,260
What should we say about Doggo?

715
00:37:34,780 --> 00:37:35,740
Think of some excuses, you all.

716
00:37:37,500 --> 00:37:38,100
Coach,

717
00:37:38,500 --> 00:37:40,260
Tu Jun had diarrhea last night

718
00:37:40,260 --> 00:37:41,060
so he's not coming today.

719
00:37:42,040 --> 00:37:42,640
That's right.

720
00:37:42,780 --> 00:37:44,020
When I visited him last night

721
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:45,100
he was

722
00:37:45,180 --> 00:37:45,940
having a hard time with it.

723
00:37:46,300 --> 00:37:47,180
He's still not well this morning.

724
00:37:47,620 --> 00:37:48,620
No, he's not.

725
00:37:53,180 --> 00:37:54,500
Go visit Tu Jun, you all.

726
00:37:55,540 --> 00:37:56,180
He bought our lie?

727
00:37:56,700 --> 00:37:58,020
We're not training today.

728
00:38:01,340 --> 00:38:02,900
His father is gone.

729
00:38:06,580 --> 00:38:08,260
How do you know his father is gone, coach?

730
00:38:10,220 --> 00:38:11,820
Tu Jun's father is gone.

731
00:38:13,840 --> 00:38:14,460
Coach,

732
00:38:15,100 --> 00:38:16,500
what do you mean by "gone"?

733
00:38:21,260 --> 00:38:23,420
I mean, he is gone from this world.

734
00:38:37,140 --> 00:38:38,700
What are you talking about!

735
00:39:00,580 --> 00:39:01,180
Doggo!

736
00:39:48,300 --> 00:39:49,260
Are the kids asleep?

737
00:39:52,260 --> 00:39:53,980
They say good things happen to good people.

738
00:39:53,980 --> 00:39:55,580
Tu was such a good person.

739
00:39:55,580 --> 00:39:57,180
Why would he end up like this?

740
00:39:58,940 --> 00:40:00,740
What should the kid do now?

741
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:04,980
The thing is, he won't say anything.

742
00:40:04,980 --> 00:40:06,580
Not even a single cry.

743
00:40:06,740 --> 00:40:08,380
As old as I am,

744
00:40:09,060 --> 00:40:11,060
I don't even know what to say to that boy.

745
00:40:11,060 --> 00:40:11,740
Yeah...

746
00:40:16,420 --> 00:40:17,620
Doggo is not feeling well.

747
00:40:18,620 --> 00:40:21,340
Go in and say something to him.

748
00:40:21,340 --> 00:40:24,340
But I don't know what to say!

749
00:40:25,300 --> 00:40:26,980
I've never experienced this.

750
00:40:33,180 --> 00:40:33,800
Jiao Jiao!

751
00:40:34,460 --> 00:40:35,060
Doggo.

752
00:40:35,660 --> 00:40:36,620
We grew up toge...

753
00:40:41,340 --> 00:40:43,300
He's having a really hard time already!

754
00:41:29,580 --> 00:41:30,980
Why's the butcher so late today?

755
00:41:31,300 --> 00:41:33,100
1 kilo of lean meat, plus a leg bone.

756
00:41:36,580 --> 00:41:37,300
You dumb or?

757
00:41:38,060 --> 00:41:39,020
Running your business or not?

758
00:41:40,220 --> 00:41:41,220
Weirdo.

759
00:41:44,060 --> 00:41:45,340
You selling your meat or not?

760
00:41:47,500 --> 00:41:48,100
Yes.

761
00:41:50,460 --> 00:41:51,100
Lean meat.

762
00:41:58,460 --> 00:41:59,380
A kilo!

763
00:41:59,660 --> 00:42:00,380
Is that enough?

764
00:42:06,540 --> 00:42:07,540
Can you cut your meat or not?

765
00:42:21,340 --> 00:42:22,460
Hurry up!

766
00:42:24,860 --> 00:42:25,860
Need me to teach you or what?

767
00:42:28,120 --> 00:42:28,740
Jun Jun,

768
00:42:28,740 --> 00:42:29,380
leave it to me.

769
00:42:38,740 --> 00:42:39,380
15 yuan.

770
00:42:47,940 --> 00:42:49,060
Tu was a good man.

771
00:42:52,220 --> 00:42:53,620
He helped me a lot.

772
00:42:55,060 --> 00:42:56,660
When some mobs were making troubles here,

773
00:42:56,660 --> 00:42:58,180
Tu protected me.

774
00:42:58,420 --> 00:42:59,820
Your dad used to mention you a lot

775
00:43:00,100 --> 00:43:01,240
before us when he was alive,

776
00:43:01,500 --> 00:43:02,100
I'm telling you.

777
00:43:02,220 --> 00:43:03,500
I miss him a lot too.

778
00:43:03,500 --> 00:43:04,740
We were all so happy together

779
00:43:04,740 --> 00:43:06,220
when he was around,

780
00:43:06,740 --> 00:43:07,780
weren't we?

781
00:43:22,540 --> 00:43:23,300
It's starting soon.

782
00:43:23,900 --> 00:43:24,900
Go inside first.

783
00:43:41,260 --> 00:43:42,700
Uncles, aunties, good to see you.

784
00:43:42,700 --> 00:43:43,260
Help yourself to the drinks.

785
00:43:43,260 --> 00:43:44,780
We're sorry for your loss. Very sorry.

786
00:43:45,020 --> 00:43:45,940
We're sorry for your loss.

787
00:43:48,220 --> 00:43:48,940
Uncles, aunties,

788
00:43:49,740 --> 00:43:50,540
help yourself to food and drinks.

789
00:43:51,340 --> 00:43:51,980
Help yourself.

790
00:43:51,980 --> 00:43:58,300
GRAVE CONDOLENCES TO MR. TU FU

791
00:43:58,300 --> 00:43:59,180
What's wrong with you all?

792
00:43:59,700 --> 00:44:00,820
Eat! Drink!

793
00:44:01,200 --> 00:44:01,800
C'mon.

794
00:44:02,200 --> 00:44:02,820
Here!

795
00:44:08,780 --> 00:44:09,440
Alright.

796
00:44:09,660 --> 00:44:10,660
Look after the other for me, will you?

797
00:44:14,260 --> 00:44:15,380
Uncles, aunties,

798
00:44:17,900 --> 00:44:20,180
Cheers! Our condolences to the loss.

799
00:44:22,740 --> 00:44:24,220
Is he really this strong?

800
00:44:25,860 --> 00:44:27,220
Can't you tell?

801
00:44:28,820 --> 00:44:30,380
So he's pretending to hold it together?

802
00:45:28,940 --> 00:45:29,560
Jun Jun.

803
00:45:35,820 --> 00:45:36,860
I am sorry.

804
00:45:41,100 --> 00:45:42,300
Mom's late.

805
00:45:44,460 --> 00:45:45,660
Mom's late.

806
00:45:49,740 --> 00:45:51,980
Mom's late...

807
00:45:55,700 --> 00:45:56,420
I'm sorry...

808
00:45:57,020 --> 00:45:57,620
Mom!

809
00:45:59,420 --> 00:46:01,980
I'm so sorry, Jun Jun...

810
00:46:05,460 --> 00:46:06,900
I'm so sorry...

811
00:46:18,260 --> 00:46:19,540
Doggo has it so hard...

812
00:46:25,620 --> 00:46:26,240
Today,

813
00:46:28,020 --> 00:46:28,940
I didn't invite anyone to cry at the funeral.

814
00:46:29,740 --> 00:46:30,660
There was no MC either.

815
00:46:32,380 --> 00:46:33,020
Tu Fu,

816
00:46:33,620 --> 00:46:34,420
was a butcher.

817
00:46:35,460 --> 00:46:36,260
And a pork dealer.

818
00:46:36,780 --> 00:46:37,580
And my old man.

819
00:46:38,460 --> 00:46:39,380
I was right next to him

820
00:46:39,700 --> 00:46:40,740
the day he left.

821
00:46:42,460 --> 00:46:43,300
It was raining that day,

822
00:46:44,420 --> 00:46:46,140
and both of us were soaking wet.

823
00:46:48,860 --> 00:46:51,420
I cried to God and the demon, but no one would answer.

824
00:46:51,780 --> 00:46:53,380
There was not a single soul around.

825
00:46:54,020 --> 00:46:54,820
You all know

826
00:46:55,060 --> 00:46:56,220
that butcher's quite a bulky man.

827
00:46:56,700 --> 00:46:57,500
I carried him on my back

828
00:46:57,940 --> 00:46:59,540
and kept running and running.

829
00:47:00,500 --> 00:47:01,340
I ran for so long.

830
00:47:02,700 --> 00:47:04,140
We finally made it to the hospital,

831
00:47:04,860 --> 00:47:06,300
but he'd lost too much blood by then

832
00:47:07,740 --> 00:47:08,940
and the doctors couldn't bring him back.

833
00:47:11,420 --> 00:47:14,020
My old man is a vulgar one,

834
00:47:14,260 --> 00:47:15,100
not very educated or cultured.

835
00:47:15,460 --> 00:47:16,580
Swears all the time.

836
00:47:16,780 --> 00:47:17,940
I'm sure you all remember that.

837
00:47:22,380 --> 00:47:23,420
I'm telling you,

838
00:47:24,540 --> 00:47:26,820
He's feet smells terrible.

839
00:47:27,900 --> 00:47:28,900
It's honestly so bad.

840
00:47:29,860 --> 00:47:30,500
Once,

841
00:47:31,380 --> 00:47:32,980
he put his shoes on the balcony.

842
00:47:33,380 --> 00:47:34,180
Then the wind blew in,

843
00:47:34,580 --> 00:47:36,660
and the whole room was ruined!

844
00:47:43,900 --> 00:47:45,020
I think he died

845
00:47:46,260 --> 00:47:47,620
because he's way too stingy.

846
00:47:49,540 --> 00:47:50,620
He's so stingy that

847
00:47:50,900 --> 00:47:52,620
he wouldn't even buy me a PHS

848
00:47:52,620 --> 00:47:53,660
which only costs a few hundred yuan.

849
00:47:54,060 --> 00:47:55,100
So, I couldn't find a phone

850
00:47:55,860 --> 00:47:56,900
to call the ambulance

851
00:47:57,660 --> 00:47:58,460
on that day.

852
00:48:06,260 --> 00:48:07,460
My dad is really so stingy.

853
00:48:08,700 --> 00:48:09,340
He...

854
00:48:09,980 --> 00:48:10,580
When I was little,

855
00:48:10,820 --> 00:48:11,500
during new year,

856
00:48:12,180 --> 00:48:13,060
all of you have presents.

857
00:48:14,140 --> 00:48:15,140
So I ran back home and asked him,

858
00:48:15,500 --> 00:48:17,060
butcher, where's my new year present?

859
00:48:19,220 --> 00:48:20,220
And butcher told me,

860
00:48:20,580 --> 00:48:21,239
he said,

861
00:48:22,140 --> 00:48:22,820
you little brat,

862
00:48:23,220 --> 00:48:25,380
your old man's got something prepared for you!

863
00:48:26,220 --> 00:48:27,180
And then,

864
00:48:27,180 --> 00:48:28,540
he threw this marinated pig head

865
00:48:28,540 --> 00:48:29,260
right at me.

866
00:48:30,020 --> 00:48:31,460
I cried so hard then.

867
00:48:32,679 --> 00:48:33,280
And then

868
00:48:33,460 --> 00:48:34,540
he hurried to console me.

869
00:48:35,820 --> 00:48:36,460
He said,

870
00:48:36,980 --> 00:48:37,740
you little brat,

871
00:48:38,100 --> 00:48:39,260
this is such fun to play with.

872
00:48:39,620 --> 00:48:40,260
This is really fun to play with.

873
00:48:40,660 --> 00:48:41,900
You can eat it when you're tired of playing with it,

874
00:48:42,220 --> 00:48:44,020
and when you're full, you can keep playing with it!

875
00:48:47,020 --> 00:48:48,100
Sometimes,

876
00:48:48,380 --> 00:48:49,620
he washes pork at home.

877
00:48:52,340 --> 00:48:53,500
He sweats a lot from washing the pork.

878
00:48:53,740 --> 00:48:54,340
And then,

879
00:48:54,580 --> 00:48:56,100
he just uses the water for washing pork

880
00:48:56,540 --> 00:48:57,540
to wash his face.

881
00:48:58,060 --> 00:48:58,980
What's more,

882
00:48:59,660 --> 00:49:00,820
you would've never guessed,

883
00:49:01,140 --> 00:49:02,900
he doesn't even rinse it

884
00:49:03,060 --> 00:49:05,460
and goes to sleep like that!

885
00:49:08,300 --> 00:49:09,260
Oh it stinks.

886
00:49:13,420 --> 00:49:14,300
Many of you

887
00:49:15,340 --> 00:49:16,380
have been to my house for meal.

888
00:49:18,500 --> 00:49:19,860
I'm sure you've all seen

889
00:49:20,540 --> 00:49:22,380
the few famous dishes of butcher.

890
00:49:23,460 --> 00:49:24,740
Pork liver fries pork.

891
00:49:25,460 --> 00:49:26,580
Pork heart fries pork.

892
00:49:27,780 --> 00:49:28,660
Pork kidney fries pork.

893
00:49:30,180 --> 00:49:32,060
He can dissect a pig

894
00:49:32,060 --> 00:49:33,780
and fry it over and over again.

895
00:49:34,580 --> 00:49:35,940
All of you think he's being generous.

896
00:49:37,180 --> 00:49:38,020
You all say,

897
00:49:38,020 --> 00:49:39,100
butcher is so generous,

898
00:49:39,620 --> 00:49:41,740
treating us to all this meat!

899
00:49:42,860 --> 00:49:44,460
But only I know that actually,

900
00:49:45,460 --> 00:49:46,980
the meat that butcher treated you to

901
00:49:47,220 --> 00:49:49,460
were all leftovers at his stall.

902
00:49:50,180 --> 00:49:51,460
And he forced you all to not waste food

903
00:49:51,900 --> 00:49:53,140
and finish it all.

904
00:49:59,820 --> 00:50:00,540
And his cooking...

905
00:50:01,820 --> 00:50:03,060
honestly sucks.

906
00:50:09,820 --> 00:50:10,660
All of you who came today

907
00:50:12,900 --> 00:50:15,300
are family and friends who care for my old man.

908
00:50:17,100 --> 00:50:18,940
And you're people that my old man cared about.

909
00:50:20,500 --> 00:50:22,060
When he left, my old man told me,

910
00:50:22,660 --> 00:50:23,260
he said,

911
00:50:24,700 --> 00:50:25,500
"Before I leave,

912
00:50:26,140 --> 00:50:28,500
I'd just like to see the smiley faces of my loved ones."

913
00:50:45,980 --> 00:50:46,660
Thank you all

914
00:50:48,220 --> 00:50:49,300
for making his last wish come true.

915
00:51:21,180 --> 00:51:21,820
Jun Jun,

916
00:51:22,460 --> 00:51:23,060
my little brat.

917
00:51:25,660 --> 00:51:26,420
I love you.

918
00:51:36,700 --> 00:51:37,580
I love you too.

919
00:51:59,900 --> 00:52:00,940
As we grew up,

920
00:52:02,180 --> 00:52:03,580
we start to understand that

921
00:52:04,500 --> 00:52:06,220
what attract us to each other

922
00:52:07,140 --> 00:52:08,540
is probably our brightness on the outside.

923
00:52:10,540 --> 00:52:12,380
But what draw us intimately close

924
00:52:13,780 --> 00:52:15,220
is the vulnerability inside us.
